ed for in currently used discrete\ndislocation dynamics models which assume the core energy to be a constant.\nUsing case studies involving simple dislocation structures, we demonstrate that\nthe contribution to the core force from the core energy dependence on\nmacroscopic deformations can be significant in comparison to the elastic\nPeach-Koehler force even up to distances of $10-15$ nm between dislocation\nstructures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Jan 2017 04:30:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Mar 2017 02:03:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-24"}
