ility normally goes undetected in\nfaster novae due to the low cadence of typical observations; implying erratic\nbehaviour is not necessarily related to the rate of decline.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Jan 2017 13:19:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 18 Feb 2017 10:26:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 15 Mar 2017 17:51:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-16"}
